#Repost @instagram
・・・
Professional footballer Paul Pogba (@paulpogba) is known for his ⚽ skills, but he recently discovered another talent... cooking.⁣⁣⁣
⁣
While at home with his family in France, he’s surprising his mom by making her one of his favorite childhood desserts. 🥮️ “I really hope my mom will love it,” says Paul. “But I hope she doesn’t eat everything because I love it too.” 😂⁣⁣
⁣
#TakeABreak with Paul (and his adorable son) as he dances and dribbles his way around the kitchen. 💯

I am PROUD OF YOU. You win some, you lose some. You took the courage to take the penalties and you showed your worth to help your country reach the final. node.text:
It’s been a dream once again to play in such a prestigious tournament and against the best nations in the world. We were not able to succeed but I would like to congratulate Italy for winning the tournament and also give a big cheer to Denmark and @chriseriksen8 for showing strength during your difficult times. Thank you again to all of the fans for your energy and positivity. I will always remember this special EUROs tournament for the rest of my life. It was great to see you all in the stadiums after a difficult 18 months. Hopefully we’ll see you soon and with the trophy! 

🇫🇷 @equipedefrance #FiersdetreBleus
